Three children have burned to death in a shack fire in Valhalla Park on Thursday.According the City of Cape Town s Fire and Rescue Services spokesperson Theo Layne, the fire was caused by an electrical short circuit.&#8220;Three children died in the fire. The cause of the fire was a short circuit in the electric wiring that had spread to the remainder of the structure. 14 Firefighters with four vehicles extinguished the fire in less than an hour,&#8221; said LayneTwo boys and a girl died. It is reported that they were between the ages of 3 and 12.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;